This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with texture synthesis from images. It could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it discusses the production of 3D textures. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) suggests that it could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of high-resolution photos suggests that it could also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
